progress.text: Sam had history of feeling more tired in the last couple of months and experienced SOB and tightness in his chest going up stairs and walking. He presented to his GP when he was complaining of indigestion. He was referred to Cardiologist and undertook a stress test, angiogram and was found to have disease in LAD, RCA and Diag. He works as a sales consultant and has a family history of heart disease with his father and uncle having had high cholesterol and stent.

Mr Jones has not had any chest pain symptoms. Discussed Chest pain action plan if he does have any symptoms. Driving restrictions reinforced and he has a friend who can help as well as using online shopping. Sternal precautions reinforced regarding weight lifting restrictions and Mr Jones states that his wound is healing well. No signs of infection. He has seen his GP since discharge and has made follow up appointments with his Surgeon and cardiologist.

Discussed with Mr Jones his sternal precautions and limits with regard to housework such as vacuuming, sweeping, laundry. He is going for walks when he is at the shops and around his house. He is finding he is getting some SOB and reinforced Chest pain action plan and encouraged him to walk slowly  and rest when needed. Discussed doing talk test during physical activity. His goal this week is to walk for 10 mins in the morning and the afternoon. Mr Jones has been taking his medications and discussed importance of taking them regularly and to ensure have enough supply. He has a local pharmacist and has been educated on his medications with a pharmacy profile.

Mr Jones stated he is feeling a bit low this week due to not being able to drive. He has a friend who visits and also his son has been able to help with housework on the weekends. Discussed with Mr Jones that it is normal to have down days. Be good to keep checking on this as if he feels that every day is a down day he may need to share his feelings with a close friend, his son or his Dr

Mr Jones has had a review with his surgeon and reduced his BP medications. Advised Mr Jones to discuss with his cardiologist his BP readings and BP medications.  Mr Jones is feeling better this week as he has been walking more and not as short of breath. Discussed importance of having a healthy heart diet and information can be found in Heart Foundation website or he can ask GP for dietician review. Alcohol recommendations discussed and Mr Jones said he has not been drinking much since his operation. Usually he will have a couple of beers on the weekend.
